    <header>
        <h1>M.S. in Bioinformatics</h1>
        <div class="subtitle">Ying Wu College of Computing · New Jersey Institute of Technology</div>
    </header>
    
    <div class="container">
        <section>
            <h2>Program Overview</h2>
            <p>The interdisciplinary M.S. in Bioinformatics program (MS-BNFO) addresses the rapidly evolving intersection of biological sciences and computational methods. The curriculum provides a strong foundation in computational tools for complex biological problems, with options for further specialization in biostatistics and computational aspects of neuroscience.</p>
            
            <div class="highlight">
                <h3>Program Highlights</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>30-credit program requiring completion of 10 courses</li>
                    <li>Option to pursue research through Master's Project and Thesis</li>
                    <li>Specialized learning paths aligned with graduate certificates</li>
                    <li>Interdisciplinary curriculum spanning computer science, mathematics, and biology</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
            <div class="card">
                <p>Applicants should have a bachelor's degree from an accredited University, in Biology or STEM. Applicants with relevant professional experience may also be accepted. Further information can be found on the <a href="https://cs.njit.edu/academics/graduate/ms-bioinf/" style="color: var(--njit-red);">program's webpage</a>.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>Specialized Learning Paths</h2>
            <p>The MS in Bioinformatics program includes courses from three related graduate certificate programs:</p>
            
            <div class="columns">
                <div class="column card">
                    <h3>Certificate in Biostatistics Essentials</h3>
                    <p>Gain expertise in statistical methods applicable to biological data analysis.</p>
                    <a href="https://catalog.njit.edu/graduate/science-liberal-arts/mathematical-sciences/statistics-for-data-science-cert/" class="button">Learn More</a>
                </div>
                
                <div class="column card">
                    <h3>Certificate in Computer Science</h3>
                    <p>Develop foundational computational and programming skills.</p>
                    <a href="https://catalog.njit.edu/graduate/computing-sciences/computer-science/computer-science-cert/" class="button">Learn More</a>
                </div>
                
                <div class="column card">
                    <h3>Certificate in Neuroscience</h3>
                    <p>Explore the computational aspects of neuroscience research.</p>
                    <a href="https://catalog.njit.edu/graduate/science-liberal-arts/biology/neuroscience-cert/" class="button">Learn More</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <p class="notes">These certificates can be earned alongside the MS degree with an appropriate selection of courses. Students are encouraged to review these program catalogs and contact the advisors of these programs.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>Curriculum</h2>
            
            <h3>Degree Requirements</h3>
            <p>The program requires the completion of 30 credits. The requirement is satisfied by taking 10 courses.</p>
            <p>Students who want to pursue research can earn up to 6 of the 30 required credits by taking the BNFO 700B Masters Project possibly followed by BNFO 701B Masters Thesis. These have special requirements described in the section 'Master's Project and Thesis Policies'.</p>
            
            <h3>Introductory Courses</h3>
